        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 3:00PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 259 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kimberling, or near Bastian, moving southeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Pulaski...
Bland...
Dublin...
Max Meadows...
Patterson...
Rocky Gap...
and Allisonia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
